### HYMN XVII

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1501701">1</span></span>His first
diffused breath is this Earth.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1501702">2</span></span>His second
diffused breath is that Firmament.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1501703">3</span></span>His third
diffused breath is that Heaven.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1501704">4</span></span>His fourth
diffused breath are those Constellations.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1501705">5</span></span>His fifth
diffused breath are the Seasons.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1501706">6</span></span>His sixth
diffused breath are the Season-groups.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1501707">7</span></span>His seventh
diffused breath is the year.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1501708">8</span></span>With one and
the same object the Gods go round the Year and  
   the Seasons follow round the Vrātya.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1501709">9</span></span>When they
surround the Sun on the day of New Moon, and that  
   time of Full Moon.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_1501710">10</span></span>That one
immortality of theirs is just an oblation.

